	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=822><span id= >Lord Caedebald</span></a><br><span id=notbold>8 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This is an odd weapon. It procs an AOE dot, which also affects the wielder. So you take damage, as do any mobs around you (so don't use it around mezzed mobs, heh, or friendly NPCs - found that out the hard way, LOL).<br><br>Fun weapon though, hits pretty hard, and the proc really does nice damage. Just toss on some MR gear and buff your MR as much as you can to minimize the negative effects.<br><br>Even with the drawbacks, I must confess I love using it - it makes me giggle maniacally when it procs...<br><br>But again, be sure to only use it in the right circumstances. As a paladin I like it 'cause I can buff my own MR, and heal myself after the proc (so other healers don't have to put up with it, hehe).<br><br>Hope that helps.<br><br>Caedebald Goldheart<br>Silver Drakes<br>Rodcet Nife</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
